      "message": "There isn\u0027t a specific case here, where Skia/Wuffs use -1/0 for an infinitely looped animation. It\u0027s subtler comparing Chromium/Wuffs, since Chromium additionally defines -2 (blink::kAnimationNone) to mean a still image.\n\nAnyway, I just dropped the \"In the general case\".",
